12/14/80  dot_tab_index.compin

Syntax:  .ifi dot_tab_index "table-title"


Function:
This compose macro adds a 'table-title' to the list of Tables in the
Table of Contents, if creation of such a list has been enabled (see
tab_on.compin.info), without putting a centered table heading on the
output page.


Arguments:
'table-title' is the title of the table, as it is to appear in the list
   of Tables (first caps, no underlines).


Notes:
1) The dot_tab_index macro is used to generate a list of Tables entry
   when, for any reason, the dot_tab macro cannot be used to create the
   table heading.
2) This macro advances the table "dot number" counter so care must be
   taken in referencing the table in the text.  The next use of the
   tab, tab_index, or tab_get_no macro resets the table "dot number"
   counter back to zero.
3) See dot_tab.compin.info, tab.compin.info,
   dot_tab_get_no.compin.info, tab_get_no.compin.info, and
   tab_on.compin.info for related information.

